GET EXPLICIT 🗣️

candid conversations. about whatever we want. 

whether it’s nipple tattooing, mental health, or your pelvic floor—we’re creating space to expand the horizons of “private” conversation. special things happen when we talk freely about our lives. touching stories are told, big laughs are had, and stronger bonds are formed. so this international women’s day and all days, let’s get together and get explicit.

Shaughnessy - Restorative Tattoo Artist 
Getting “Explicit” about: Nipple Tattooing 

“It’s really frustrating because I want to show people what’s available for them. But Instagram, TikTok, and Facebook will delete my posts right away. I guess I’m flattered that it looks realistic and people are falling for it, but it should be allowed.”

Link in @hillbergandberk bio.

LOS ANGELES 🖤
march 5 —  10am - late
690 imperial st., los angeles, ca

excited to announce our collaboration with @lepapillon.studio, @studiosashiko and @bestwishes_la. please join us for our tattoo pop-up tomorrow, march 5th starting at 10am at @studiosashiko’s los angeles location. we will be hosting a lineup of talented, highly acclaimed tattoo artists with live music, limited edition merch, and more. our goal is to bring the community together with an opportunity to meet interesting, creative people as well as celebrate tattoo culture. even if you don’t get a tattoo, we welcome you to come hangout and enjoy some food, drinks and chats with us.
each artist will have their individual flash designs available. we won’t be taking appointments, it will a first come first served basis. this is a 21+ event, you must bring id.

can’t wait to see you there!

we always said “one day we will visit japan” but with our schedules it never seemed possible.

when we got married 5 years ago we said “let’s go to japan for our honeymoon” but again, running a few businesses and our hectic work schedule, we didn’t feel like we could leave for a minimum of 2 weeks.

fast forward to 5 years later and we decided that we would finally make the time to visit japan for our anniversary.
